<p>These toosl complement each other. BrowZine is journal-centric (‚Äútell me when <em>American Historical Review</em> publishes something new‚Äù). Google Scholar is topic- and author-centric (‚Äútell me when someone publishes on <em>digital labor in the Progressive Era</em>‚Äù).</p>

