</ul>

<h3 id="2-create-topic-alerts-10-min">2. Create topic alerts (10 min)</h3>

<ul>
  <li>On the Google Scholar homepage, run a search for a topic important to your research</li>
  <li>At the bottom left of the results page, click the <strong>envelope icon</strong> or ‚ÄúCreate Alert‚Äù</li>
  <li>Enter your email and confirm</li>
  <li>Scholar will email you when new papers match that search</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Tips for good alerts:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>Be specific enough to avoid noise: ‚Äúdigital labor Progressive Era‚Äù will serve you better than ‚Äúlabor history‚Äù</li>
  <li>Use quotes for exact phrases: <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">"spatial humanities"</code></li>
  <li>Create 3‚Äì5 alerts to start ‚Äî you can always adjust later</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Exercise:</strong> Create 3 alerts ‚Äî one broad (your subfield), one narrow (your specific topic), and one for a key author or scholar whose work you always want to see.</p>

<h3 id="3-follow-specific-authors-5-min">3. Follow specific authors (5 min)</h3>

